	"title": "Week 8",
	"content": "<h1 class=\"page-title\">Week 8</h1>\n  \n  <div id=\"todo-date-mount-point\"></div>\n  \n    <p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Overview</span></strong></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'NimbusSanL';\">Risk and risk premium, risk-free asset, portfolio algebra (storing return statistics in matrices and matrix operations), investment opportunity set, utility and risk aversion, optimal portfolio allocation with or without risk-free assets (minimum variance portfolio, efficient frontier, tangency portfolio, capital market line), Sharpe's ratio, solutions to the optimal portfolio allocation problem (formula for the optimal allocation between risk-free asset and tangency portfolio), one-fund separation results<br></span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'NimbusSanL';\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Learning Objectives</span></strong></p>\n<p>Upon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>how we measure absolute risk via return volatility or variance</li>\n<li>risk premium as compensation for bearing risk</li>\n<li>how to use matrices to store return statistics more efficiently</li>\n<li>the role of risk aversion and utility</li>\n<li>how to build the investment opportunity set of a given set of assets</li>\n<li>how to build the efficient frontier of an investment opportunity set</li>\n<li>how to find the tangency portfolio using Sharpe's ratio</li>\n<li>how to find the optimal allocation between risk-free asset and the tangency portfolio</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Preparation for class</span></strong></p>\n<p>Mandatory reading:</p>\n<p>Lecture 4: <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"lecture 4.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81174158?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81174158\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">lecture 4.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81174158/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download lecture 4.pdf</span></a></span></p>\n<p>Lecture 4 supplement: <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"lecture 4 sup.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81173657?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81173657\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">lecture 4 sup.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/course